---
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Math from '../components/Math.astro';
---

<Section id="optimal-stress" number="6" title={"Agents vs. optimal stress " + "Σ₀*(N)"}>
  <figure>
    <div
      class="grid place-items-center text-center text-[var(--color-muted)]"
      style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 3; background: var(--color-figure-bg); font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.9rem;"
    >
      Figure 4. Optimal stress Σ₀*(N) vs. crowd size <em>N</em><br />
      (pending: figure from teammate)
    </div>
    <figcaption>
      <strong>Figure 4.</strong> Optimal stress
      <Math tex={String.raw`\Sigma_0^{*}(N)`} /> vs. crowd size
      <Math tex={String.raw`N`} />. The optimum decreases monotonically with
      <Math tex={String.raw`N`} />; the dashed line marks the critical crowd size
      <Math tex={String.raw`N^{*} = \mu A / (2\pi\kappa\ell^{2})`} />,
      beyond which sustained collective panic is guaranteed.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>
    The optimal stress <em>decreases</em> monotonically with crowd size.
    Larger <Math tex={String.raw`N`} /> raises mean density
    <Math tex={String.raw`\rho \approx N/A`} />, which raises
    <Math tex={String.raw`\Gamma = 2\pi\rho\ell^{2}`} />, which raises
    <Math tex={String.raw`R_0`} />. The epidemic threshold is crossed when
    <Math tex={String.raw`N > N^{*} = \mu A / (2\pi\kappa\ell^{2})`} />:
    for <Math tex={String.raw`N > N^{*}`} />, sustained panic is guaranteed above a
    threshold stress that decreases with <Math tex={String.raw`N`} />, shifting the
    optimal <Math tex={String.raw`\Sigma_0^{*}`} /> leftward. Near the
    bottleneck, local density can be three to four times the room
    average, pushing <Math tex={String.raw`R_0`} /> above 1 even when the crowd
    appears sparse globally.
  </p>

  <p>
    This result has direct design implications. Crowd managers can raise
    <Math tex={String.raw`N^{*}`} /> and widen the safe operating window by:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      reducing density <Math tex={String.raw`\rho`} /> via wider exits or staggered
      entry, shifting <Math tex={String.raw`R_0`} /> below 1;
    </li>
    <li>
      reducing contagion strength <Math tex={String.raw`\kappa`} /> via authoritative
      audio instructions that give agents an alternative information
      channel, reducing susceptibility to neighbour-driven panic;
    </li>
    <li>
      reducing contagion length <Math tex={String.raw`\ell`} /> via physical
      separators that block line of sight, shortening the range of social
      influence.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    Each lever corresponds to a measurable architectural or procedural
    intervention. The broader takeaway: the alarm intensity and crowd
    density appropriate for a 20-person fire drill are dangerously
    mismatched for a 500-person concert venue.
  </p>
</Section>
